article.description: — Malek Green came off the bench to score 16 points to lift Canisius to a 67-64 win over Siena on Saturday.
article.headline: Green scores 16 to lead Canisius over Siena 67-64
article.linkText: Green scores 16 to lead Canisius over Siena 67-64
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- — Malek Green came off the bench to score 16 points to lift Canisius to a 67-64 win over Siena on Saturday. Ahamadou Fofana had 13 points and six steals for Canisius (11-20, 7-13 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Armon Harried added 11 points and six rebounds. Xzavier Long had 2 points and 11 rebounds. Jackson Stormo had 18 points and 11 rebounds for the Saints (15-13, 12-8). Colby Rogers added 17 points. Anthony Gaines had six rebounds. The Golden Griffins evened the season series against the Saints. Siena defeated Canisius 73-65 on Feb. 1. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
